    "type": "Requirement",
    "name": "CPB Hemolysis CFD Model Requirements",
    "description": "The computational model shall predict relative hemolysis index (RH) with sufficient accuracy to support device tolerance decisions. The model shall be validated against experimental hemolysis data for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. Boundary conditions shall reflect clinical CPB operating ranges of 2–6 L/min flow and 1500–3500 RPM rotational speed. Mesh independence shall be demonstrated via Richardson extrapolation. Turbulence model selection shall be justified by comparison to benchmark data. The model shall reproduce predicate device hemolysis trends within ±15% across all five evaluated flow-speed combinations."
  },
